    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your slow cooker and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Turn on your <strong>slow cooker</strong> to high</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-in-black-bean-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferable non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced beef</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-in-black-bean-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-in-black-bean-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the beef has browned, add the <strong>onion wedges </strong>and your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> to the pan with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>black bean paste</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>with<strong> </strong>250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil, once boiling, transfer everything from the pan to the <strong>slow cooker </strong>and give everything a good mix up, then cover and cook on high for an initial 2 hours</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-in-black-bean-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-in-black-bean-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After an initial 2 hours, add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> and cook for a further 2 hours \u2013 this is your <strong>slow cooker beef in black bean</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-in-black-bean-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the black bean beef has 25 min left, rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-in-black-bean-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>slow cooker beef in black bean </strong>with the <strong>cooked rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
